-- Portuguese Bonds Lead Euro Peripheral Debt Declines on Austerity Concern
-- B y   P a u l   D o b s o n
-- 2010-09-24T13:53:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/portuguese-bonds-lead-euro-peripheral-debt-declines-on-austerity-concern.html
German government bonds fell,
sending the 10-year yield 4 basis points higher to 2.33 percent
as of 2:50 p.m. in London.  The extra yield investors demand to hold Portuguese 10-year
debt instead of German securities was little changed at 401
basis points after widening to a record 420 basis points. The
difference in yield, or spread, between benchmark bunds and
Irish bonds narrowed 3 basis points to 415 basis points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
